<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTING BANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article "Drawing a Bead on Hunting" (Part I, Aug. 28) would lead readers to 
believe that the current effort to save the mountain lion is an anti-hunting 
campaign. Such is not the case. The California Wildlife Initiative, if passed 
by the voters in 1990, will not stop all hunting and is not intended to do so. 
</P>
<P>
The number of mountain lions left in California is unknown. No scientific study 
has been made to determine the number of these creatures left in our state. 
Until such a study is made it would seem prudent to stop the hunting of 
mountain lions. 
</P>
<P>
Even so, the initiative has provisions for the taking of lions which endanger 
people or kill rancher's livestock. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID ADAMS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
