<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTBALL SHOW WILL GO ON AT OAK PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN WATERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite uncertainty over the number of available players and the absence of a 
head coach, Oak Park High will field a football team for tonight's game against 
Boron, Oak Park officials confirmed Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Oak Park will play host to Boron in the opener at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
"Our kids told us they want to play so we're playing Friday night," Athletic 
Director Fred Yamano said. "We will continue with normal procedure. We will 
hold a pregame meal tonight (Thursday) and then have a walk-through practice." 
</P>
<P>
Ron Veres, who claimed he had only eight healthy players, resigned Wednesday 
after two years as Oak Park's coach. Yamano has not selected a successor. In 
the interim, Yamano will run the team along with former assistant Roger Newell, 
school Principal Jeff Chancer and the remaining varsity and junior varsity 
coaches. SEAN WATERS 
</P>
