<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Trump Card," a new syndicated bingo-like TV game show backed by real estate 
tycoon Donald Trump, has been tripped up by some last-minute contractual 
problems. Trump was set to make the official announcement Thursday morning at 
Trump Tower in New York City, but that press conference was canceled late 
Wednesday. However, a Lorimar executive said "Trump Card" is almost sure to be 
on the market in January at the annual National Assn. of Television Program 
Executives convention for a debut next fall. Trump will own a third of the 
program, as will both Lorimar Television and Warner Bros. Domestic Television 
Distribution. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
