<SECTION>
<P>
Part 1; Page 2; Column 5; National Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
59 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman who used the "battered spouse" defense against charges she killed her 
lesbian lover was convicted of second-degree murder in West Palm Beach, Fla. 
Annette Green, 30, was found guilty by a jury in the 1988 shooting death of her 
11-year lover, Ivonne Julio. Defense attorney William Lasley had said that 
Julio beat and tormented Green for years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
