<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN EXTREMIS WINS FEATURE AT DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEL MAR 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Extremis took the lead with a sixteenth of a mile to go and pulled away for 
a 1 1/2-length victory in the $60,000 feature race on the turf course at Del 
Mar Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
In Extremis, ridden by Laffit Pincay, covered 1 1/16 miles over a firm course 
in 1:43 1/5 and earned $33,000 in the race for 3-year-olds and up. 
</P>
<P>
In Extremis paid $5, $2.60 and $2.40. 
</P>
<P>
Fair Judgment, ridden by Gary Stevens, was bumped hard in the initial strides 
of the race by In Extremis and Bon Vent but finished second, paying $2.60 and 
$2.20. 
</P>
<P>
Bon Vent, ridden by Robbie Davis, finished third and paid $2.80. 
</P>
