<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOSSEN, BROUSSARD LEAD WASHINGTON ST. TO 46-41 VICTORY OVER BRIGHAM YOUNG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PROVO, Utah 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brad Gossen passed for 317 yards and two touchdowns, and Steve Broussard caught 
a 66-yard scoring pass and ran for three other touchdowns as Washington State 
defeated No. 24-ranked Brigham Young, 46-41, Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Gossen threw scoring passes of 64 and 66 yards in the first half to Tim 
Stallworth and Broussard. 
</P>
<P>
Washington State (2-0) bounced back from a 21-17 halftime deficit as Broussard 
scored twice on one-yard runs in the third quarter and Jason Hanson kicked a 
58-yard field goal, breaking the school record of 57 yards set by Paul Watson 
in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
Hanson also had field goals of 22, 52 and 46 yards, tying a school record for 
the most field goals in a game, and extended his string of successful 
conversions to a school-record 54. 
</P>
<P>
Ty Detmer of BYU (1-1) completed 34 of 53 passes for 537 yards and four 
touchdowns, but he had three passes intercepted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
