<P>
Mazda Weighs a Luxury Line: Mazda Motor of America Inc. has formed a task force 
to study whether it should produce a luxury car for the U.S. market to compete 
with other Japanese auto makers' upscale lines. Toyota Motor Corp., Nissan 
Motor Co. and Honda Motor Co. either have or will by the end of the year have 
luxury car divisions in the United States. The announcement was the first 
official indication that Mazda might do the same. 
</P>
