<P>
Many pleasure boaters do not understand the dangers of sailing near large 
commercial ships and are involved in an increasing number of collisions that 
could have been prevented, shipping industry officials said in San Francisco. 
The waterways are crowded with water skiers, jet skiers and windsurfers who are 
risking serious accidents because they do not understand how fast ships travel 
or other dangers, according to the American Waterways Operators, the national 
association of representing the tugboat and barge industry 
