</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Manila court began hearing an $810-million lawsuit against Ferdinand E. 
Marcos based on the former president's tax returns. It is the first case 
against Marcos that has gone to trial in the Philippines since he was ousted 
three years ago. In all, the government has filed 35 civil suits since 1987 to 
recover $100 billion that Marcos and 300 associates are accused of stealing 
during his 24 years in power. 
