ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
CITY TO SPONSOR BOOTH AT TRADE FAIR IN JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fullerton has decided to set up a booth to promote the city during a November 
trade fair in Fukui, Japan, city officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
The Fullerton booth at the Fukui trade fair will include a video narrated in 
Japanese, photographs and information about the city, and perhaps sample 
products from Fullerton manufacturers. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council unanimously agreed earlier this week to send the display 
materials to Fukui and create a formal sister-city relationship. The council 
budgeted up to $15,000 for sister-city activities. 
</P>
<P>
Fukui joins Morelia, Mexico, as Fullerton's other sister city. 
</P>
<P>
For the past few years, groups in Fullerton and Fukui have participated in 
student exchanges and visits, and Fukui then asked Fullerton to become its 
sister city. 
</P>
