<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
FRIEND IS SUSPECTED IN SHOOTING DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police in Anaheim were searching Thursday for a 38-year-old man they said is 
suspected of shooting and killing a longtime friend in his home and then 
fleeing. 
</P>
<P>
Officers found the body of Lee Madison Fox slumped in the bedroom of his house 
in the 1500 block of South Dallas Drive with a gunshot wound to the head. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors told police that Fox had arrived home shortly before 10 p.m. on 
Wednesday with a friend, said Sgt. Chet Barry. It was unclear where the two men 
had been earlier, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Within minutes, neighbors reported, a gunshot was heard and the friend ran from 
the home, Barry said. When officers arrived, they discovered Fox's body leaning 
against a hide-a-bed inside his single-family home. 
</P>
<P>
Officers recovered the apparent weapon, a revolver, Barry said, and interviewed 
neighbors who were acquainted with both men. However, investigators failed to 
come up with a motive for the slaying, Barry said. 
</P>
