<P>
3 MERCEDES BOUGHT FOR BAKKERS, COURT TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHARLOTTE, N.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Bakker's PTL ministry bought the evangelist and his family three Mercedes 
cars for $150,000 three years ago even though the organization was having cash 
flow problems, its former budget director testified today at Bakker's fraud 
trial. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Burgund told the court that Bakker wanted a Mercedes for his wife, Tammy 
Faye, because her Cadillac had been wrecked in an accident. 
</P>
<P>
