<P>
3 ARAB COLLABORATION SUSPECTS SLAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Palestinians suspected of collaborating with Israeli authorities were 
found dead today in the occupied territories, and the army said it arrested 
four Arabs in one of the slayings. 
</P>
<P>
The deaths raised to 110 the number of Palestinians killed by fellow Arabs 
since the start nearly 21 months ago of the uprising against Israeli 
occupation. Most have been accused of collaboration. The slayings came despite 
an appeal in a leaflet distributed by the uprising's leadership calling on 
Palestinian activists to not be too quick to kill alleged collaborators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
